JOHANNESBURG - Democratic Alliance (DA) chief whip John Steenhuisen has explained his comments earlier this week about his party's leadership. Speaking on the sidelines of the DA's federal congress, which is underway in Johannesburg this weekend, he explained why he is against the extension of the party’s presidential term from three to five years. WATCH: Maimane sets tone for party's federal congress Leadership issues, the ongoing spat with Patricia de Lille, and racial quotas are among the contentious talking points at the congress. You can watch the interview with Steenhuisen in the video box above. eNCA